reviews_data.review_text: Great place to play card games
They let me experience the delusion of each magic pack costing $5 in their commander sealed league (it's a blast).

This place is awesome.  I'd never have expected so much charm to fit into one little store.  I first visited for an FNM draft of Edge of Eternities with my son.  They were very accommodating of him as a new player, and we both had a great time.  The set was space themed, and my son (astute as he is) asked if some of the decor in the shop (some framed astronaut pictures and other subtle touches here and there) were set up specifically for this set.  I answered a clear and authoritative "No." I, an adult human being, seasoned in the harsh and cruel world of our time, clearly know that no one would go to such effort to do something like that, charming as it may be.

But lo!  I was quickly corrected, and, frankly, bewildered, that someone had taken the time and effort to add such a beautiful, but subtle touch for the benefit of the handful of nerds that spend their evenings turning cardboard sideways.  Since then, I've been continuously impressed with the venue, whether it be for the ambience, friendly staff, welcoming crowd, or outstanding value (a night out for two for only $30? Yes, please!)

Seriously, I can't recommend this place enough.  If you like to get your planeswalk on (they've got tons of other games to!), this is the perfect place to do it.

Chill atmosphere, chiller staff. Everyone here is extremely friendly and welcoming. They run a ton of events that are easy to join and a blast to play. I definitely recommend if you're new to board games or card games, and especially if you're looking for your local gaming store to join.
Such a great place! Steven was so helpful and the place was sooo clean and well curated!

This is such an amazing place. I came here for my first magic prerelease and it was awesome. Everyone was super friendly and the staff was so so great. Thank you guys so much!! Im already planning my trip back!

Great vibes great people the owner is super cool. Love this pace.

They have a great selection of board games, if you’re into magic the gathering they have that as well. Probably my favorite place around the area to just hang around and play board games

Went there for the first time today. Couldn’t have been a better experience. While I typically am looking for older stuff (collecting vintage RPG ephemera), a shop like this warms my heart. The shop was packed with families and friends all playing games together. A place like this just didn’t exist for me when I was a kid and if it did, it certainly wasn’t as welcoming or friendly to newcomers or non-regulars.

The two gentlemen who answered my questions were delightful and kind and even gave me a free sticker! Little things like that always make me smile. It’s clearly a hopping spot and now I have a place to go to learn one of their dozens and dozens of board games.

Also, they sell beer which, c’mon now, that’s just awesome. Great shop, great atmosphere, will be back.
Excellent cozy and comfortable space to play games and buy games!

This is business is a gem in our community.  For $5 you can get a table, borrow one of their board games (see image) and play games with your friends and family.  The staff are very welcoming and went out of their way their way to make game recommendations that were a perfect match for our group. The room with the tables was modern and very clean.  I am a middle age woman and there was no judgement, it is a space for people of all ages.  They have a private room that fits up to 10 people and you can reserve for the very reasonable price of $25.  If you like one of the games you borrow they will deduct the $5 table fee from the price of the game if you purchase.  I couldn't recommend this place more!  (Pro tip: If you want to use the tables on the weekends, plan on going after 5 pm.  They often have events during the daytime)
Thrilled to have TTT nearby - it’s a warm, welcoming space where I’ve enjoyed countless games with my kids and fellow players. No other local store creates the same sense of community.

Great shop for friends and families to enjoy board games and collectible card games like Magic and Lorcana. Employees are knowledgeable and welcoming. Great selection of drinks and snacks (craft beers and baked goods!).
I wish my town had a shop this great!
Its a great experience with a variety of both board games and trading card games.  Love coming here

I go here at least once a month with my daughter, and we ALWAYS have a great time! I always feel welcomed and I love the board game variety. I’ve learned many new games thanks to this place! It is now a tradition for me 😊

Bought cards here a few times and finally popped in - such an awesome space for games with a warm community. Folks working were super accommodating and answered any questions we had + other customers were super friendly - with those playing similar games offering a match! Family friendly, clean, air conditioned, and Star Wars fans check out the bathroom!

Absolutely love coming to To The Table! Benson and the staff are always extremely welcoming and every time I’ve come in with my now 7 month old they always ask how she’s doing and treat her like she’s one of the community since since she has been coming with me the store since she was 3 months old.

Not only are the staff and community they’ve cultivated amazing, the atmosphere in the store is also second to none. The shop is always clean, organized and stocked with so many options for Magic the Gathering.

If you’re looking for a top-tier LGS, look no further than To The Table!
The store cancelled my $1700 order because the market price went up
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hey Don - we cancelled your order immediately after you placed it, and told you why. Sorry you’re frustrated with that!

-Benson

reviews_data.review_text: Very cool place to buy board and card games. They have a good selection of games to play and games to buy. If they don’t have something in stock, the owners will order it for you. The games are reasonably priced unlike a lot of local board game stores and the owners are super cool. The store is very family friendly. The store owner tries to keep the language family friendly and my wife and I love going in there with our baby to play games. I highly recommend it.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you! Glad you enjoyed our shop ♥️

reviews_data.review_text:
Benson is the best, and TTT is my favorite game store I've ever had the pleasure of going to (and since moving to NC in 2022, I've tried every place around Charlotte).

You will always be welcomed on coming in and if you are looking for a game, they will be extremely happy (and detailed) on helping you find something to try. They have a ton of games available for you to play as part of the $5 table fee and you can play/switch games as much as you want. Seriously, if you are looking for a place to hang out with friends and play card/tabletop games, this is 100% the place to go.

Five stars for sure! My favorite place in the Charlotte area to play cards & boardgames at.

The area is clean, well-maintained, and organized. On the dozen different times I've been the staff has always been punctual & polite. Whether it's answering my questions about upcoming products, helping me to sell/trade my personal collection or even going out of their name way to custom-order things upon request it really is great experience every time.

Cannot recommend this place enough. I went here with my boyfriend for the first time, as he loves board games, and we immediately made plans to return. They have a huge selection of board games to rent at a super fair price of 5$ for a table for as long as you want, and even more games for sale at better prices than most department stores. The staff is super welcoming and friendly and checks in frequently to make sure you're enjoying your time there, even on busier days. They have lots of super cool events for all interests- my boyfriend loves strategy board games, so he attended board gaming night, and I prefer social games, so I attended Blood on the Clocktower. We've had a blast every time we go. Perfect for date nights, friend get-togethers, family outings, or even going solo and finding new friends.

Shop is a nice gem to have in the small board/card analog gaming community.

Clean, good snacks. Friendly staff. Played there a couple times with my family to add some extra players to my games.
Hands down the best game store I have ever visited. Owner and staff are all extremely friendly and accommodating. Excellent selection as well. Could not recommend highly enough

This shop is fantastic! Ive been going here for little more than a year now and partake in the weekly Friday night magic draft events and more recently blood on the clock tower. All the staff are super friendly are as dedicated to the hobby as I am. Play space is nice and spacious with an incredible selection of board games to try and buy. The private room has an incredible theme and host larger parties for their D&D or large group board games. I will be enjoying my time here for many years to come!

This place is an absolute treasure to the city. I have been to some other places but the staff and community of this store is so incredibly welcoming and a joy to be around. They have an excellent selection of games, great events occasionally, fair board game prices, etc. This place is the place to go if you are ever wanting to get into board games or are looking for others to play board games with. Thank you so much for everything yall have done.

Benson and his team are incredible. My fiancé and I have been going here since before its hard launch last year. It has been a great and consistent safe haven for all my friends and I. Super inclusive, nonjudgmental, and diverse group of fellow board game nerds 🤓
It is very apparent the owner and his staff care about the business they’re in and keeping their patrons safe. 🖤 TTT always has my business!!

Amazing place with the BEST people! If you’re looking to find a community here’s the place!

I’d also like to specifically call out my personal experience with children at the store. They host Blood on the Clocktower events on Saturdays (social deduction game) where I’ve played with a 10 year old and a 6 month old. To The Table was super inclusive and accommodating. It’s never been a problem and I’ve been going there every week since they opened.

Overall, this is a great place with great people. And delicious treats, too - Oatmeal pie is my fav!

Been there a few times.  They're setup is peak. They have a wide variety of games to purchase and play at the store, reasonably priced. Staff is always friendly. They also host occasional events welcomed to the public to play a learn/game. I've been playing a lot of the public social deduction game there, Blood on the Clock Tower.

Whether you’re a serious or casual board gamer, To The Table is a great place to have fun and meet people. The staff is so kind and welcoming and there are a lot of fun organized events to get in on. Highly recommend to anyone in the area!
Rude staff and it seems that the cafe only caters to a certain demographic. I think some players spend more time shuffling their decks than freshening up.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hey there - this appears to be related to a review we've already responded to. Sorry you feel that way!

reviews_data.review_text: I've been playing Trading Card Games for over 3 years now and have been to almost all of the Hobby shops/collectible card shops in the greater Charlotte area. I have to say that this is probably the top 2 or even 1 shop I've been to! Prices have always been fair (way better than online prices or even locally), they stock the best sleeves (Katanas) and have a great community and staff. From my experience they're primarily a Magic The Gathering store with a Star Wars Unlimited community as well. This review comes from primarily being a card game player but I know they also carry a ton of board games and have a board game player base as well!

I've never been to a game/card shop with such a good atmosphere. Employees are fair, friendly, helpful. Shop is good for kids even my smaller kids have been able to play several games from their library, and they love the bathrooms vibes :joy:
Took my two little boys Rob and Jeff to play some games and they enjoyed it. Great atmosphere and wonderful staff! Will definitely be coming back!

Best shop in town. Great selection of board games,  coffee/drinks and fresh baked goods and good vibes from owners and staff. Great Magic the Gathering scene, including sealed commander leagues, premodern , and Friday night magic always fires drafts. I go out of my way and pass other LGSs to play here.

You'll be hard pressed to find a store that is more friendly, more knowledgable, more diverse, and more stocked with any game you could want (and if they don't have it, they'll order it for you).

The staff goes above and beyond here to make sure you feel welcome every time you walk through the front door.

In an area with many great game shops, this one stands above the rest.

Discovered that their was a card/board game shop about 10 minutes from my house so I decided to check it out. I enjoy playing MTG with friends and also play yugioh and pokemon more competitively so I figured I'd check it out. As far as card games are concerned, the shop primarily focuses on MTG. Playing here has been fun and the staff is friendly and knowledgeable. A majority of the people I've played with have been kind and fun to play with as someone who doesn't typically play a ton of magic in person. The store itself is well stocked with board games/tcg products/drinks and snacks. Overall, this place is definitely a gem for board game/tcg fans in the area

Rude staff, not family friendly.

Owner and staff believe this is an adult establishment, do not bother to bring children of any ages, the ownership has made it clear they’re unwelcome.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hey there - this appears to be related to a review we've already responded to. Sorry you feel that way!

reviews_data.review_text: Fantastic store, with fantastic employees. Always welcoming super knowledgeable and very fair pricing. Highly recommend, I drive past several game stores to come here weekly. Their events and general good will towards their customers will keep me coming back

Kids not welcome. I’m very sad our visit ended horribly. The place is nicely decorated and has a great atmosphere. Prices are good and the cashier was super nice and was incredibly helpful. Unfortunately, I left crying.

Not sure if it’s the owner or manger but he seemed uncomfortable with my two small kids in the store even though they were well behaved and we kept to ourselves playing a game. After a few hours, my son needed a diaper change. There is no changing table or anyway to change a diaper in the bathroom, so I quickly and discretely, changed his diaper on the bench and threw it in the trash. We were debating which Pokémon set to get my daughter when the manager/owner came up to me and told me I can’t change a diaper on the bench and that it was completely unacceptable. I told him there was no changing table and he said they are not trying to be accommodating to people like us. He also said it was unacceptable to put “something like that” in their trash. He was so rude about it that I gathered our stuff, grabbed the diaper out of the trash and left in tears.

I’m heartbroken because I was so excited to find another game store and took my family here for Father’s Day but we will not be back. Nice store for adults but no sympathy or accommodations for children or parents. If you have little kids go to Your Local Game Store. The owner Tim has young kids, kids are welcome, and there is a changing table in the bathroom.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
I wasn't there, I was out for Father's Day with my 6 month old. We've had hundreds of families in our shop, and they are always welcome. In short, your children were disruptive, you were inappropriate, my staff told you so. You're right about one thing though - Your Local Game Store is a great establishment and I would encourage you to go there in the future.

-Benson (the owner)

reviews_data.review_text: An absolute treasure of a spot, whether you're looking to try some new board games with friends or family or looking for TCG events, owner and staff are incredible and have built a great community here
Hidden Gem

What a fantastic little spot this is locally to the wider Charlotte area. Incredibly accommodating and cozy, has a great selection of games and Magic Product and they have fostered a wonderfully supportive and welcoming community.

I went in as a first timer to commander and had a great play experience. The space is cozily lit and comfortable.

Pricing is honestly phenomenal compared to other locations within the area. I couldn’t recommend the space more to people interested in getting game time in with friends, loved ones, or even trying to meet new play groups. I will come back many many times.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you, happy to welcome you to our community!

reviews_data.review_text: This place has a great selection of games and a fun atmosphere. The owner is super friendly. The snacks are great. We love this spot for a game night.
Wonderful location to host our DnD sessions. I never thought you could win DnD until I met Mike, but if you believe in Mike, he can make anything happen ❤️!
Awesome game shop!
Friendly staff, nice selection
Dunkin was really friendly and helpful. Great games, nice atmosphere, good tables. What's not to love? My wife and I had a blast our first time here.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much! Glad you had a good time.

reviews_data.review_text:
I was in town visiting and looked up a local shop on the MTG locator in order to find a draft to play in.

I called the the store to confirm and then showed up and was amazed and how well organized and stocked the shop was.

The owner couldn't have been nicer along with the other people I met at the event. I wish I lived closer and I will be sure to go out of my way to support this shop and travel in for events when I can.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for the kind words, glad you enjoyed our shop!

reviews_data.review_text: They have a great board game and card game selection, competitive prices, and fun times to be had! This is a literal Mom and Pop store with a welcoming atmosphere and daily events, great snacks, and relaxing music to enjoy gaming to!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you Asa for the kind words!

reviews_data.review_text: This place is AMAZING! A little on the small side but great atmosphere. Mike cares about his customers and is focused on building a great gaming community. Awesome place to meet folks and play games.
Please support this business great experience!
Great place to come and try out new games
Great game store with tables to sit and play. They have some drinks and snacks to enjoy as well.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for the kind words!

reviews_data.review_text: My partner and I visited a few days ago and it felt like being in your friend's basement for game night in the best way. The owner, Mike, was welcoming to every customer, attentive with our drinks/snacks/gameplay, and knowledgable about the games. He made us feel at home and it is so so clear that a lot of love and passion went into creating To The Table. The place is BEAUTIFUL. Clean, cozy, fantasy-themed but not too over the top--there's even a special room for DND or other private events. I cannot recommend this place enough for experienced gamers and board game newbies alike. A must visit!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you, hope to see you again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: Such a chill place. Everyone there was super kind, and the board game selection was really great. It was also super clean and smelled really nice which is awesome :)
Great atmosphere, FNM draft was fun.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for stopping by, we appreciate the kind words!

reviews_data.review_text: My family went this weekend to check out this spot and I am so happy we did. The selection of games you could play and purchase were both great. Mike the owner was behind the counter and was super helpful, approachable, and genuinely kind while not being super pushy to make a purchase at all. We ended up buying a game that was new to us Agricola which Mike said a lot of "more serious" board game players have in their home collection. We did not sit down and play here yet ( we have an almost 2 year old so unsure when we will be able to do that) however there were a bunch of people playing and it looked like it was spacious, well lit, and comfortable. They have local coffee, a bunch of snacks and drinks and honestly this is just the type of spot you love to see exist in our community.
Did the bloomburrow prerelease here and it was a great experience, awesome venue
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for attending our event, we're happy you had a good time!

reviews_data.review_text: Beautiful store with great relaxing atmosphere.  Themed surprises that make you smile.  Michael Benson (the owner)  is very knowledgeable and always there to help and give advice if needed.  I would highly recommend this.  You will have a LOT of fun.
Really cool spot to meet friends and play games. Great selection of games to play along with games to buy at a great price.
reviews_data.owner_answer: We're glad you dig our place!

reviews_data.review_text: It's a fantastic place, lots of games, service is excellent, the coffee is wonderful and the price is fair and very cheap
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you! We're so glad you enjoyed your visit.

reviews_data.review_text: Absolutely wonderful and friendly place. Great place for date night!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Awesome having you with us and hope to see you again!

reviews_data.review_text:
I recently ordered some Star Wars Unlimited decks from To The Table Board Game Cafe, and I have nothing but praise for their service! Navigating their online store was a breeze, with an intuitive layout and a secure checkout process that gave me peace of mind. The range of shipping options was impressive, allowing me to choose one that perfectly suited my timeline and budget.

My cards arrived right on schedule and were carefully packed. I'm very happy with the quality of both the products and the service. This was an excellent shopping experience from start to finish, and I am definitely planning to order from them again.

Highly recommend To The Table Board Game Cafe for anyone looking for a reliable and customer-friendly game store! 5 stars all the way!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Glad you received your stuff and thank you for choosing us!

reviews_data.review_text: Omg what a great place to play games. Exciting atmosphere with an enormous volume of games to play. Mike is very knowledgeable of the entire library of games
Fantastic layout of gaming tables. Nice selection of games and cards. Friendly folks. Definitely a winner.

This is the game store I have dreamed of having in Charlotte for years now.  Owner has done everything right.  Solid wood tables, great seating, comfortable temperature even when it's 100+ degrees outside.  Great parking.  Awesome vibe - feel very comfortable being there.   Great prices on MTG.   The best MTG spot in Charlotte.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much, we're glad you love the store and so happy to have you as a new friend! 😭

reviews_data.review_text:
This place is phenomenal. It's impeccably clean, boasts a vibrant and inviting atmosphere, and offers exceptionally fair pricing. The facility is beautifully maintained, providing a quiet and cozy environment that's perfect for gaming.

Highlights:
1. Game Selection:
- The game library is extensive and meticulously curated, offering a fantastic selection of games to play.
- If you can't find what you're looking for, they have an even larger selection of games available for purchase at very competitive prices. A lot of the games here were even cheaper than what I could find online.

2. Amenities:
- They offer an array of drinks, small snacks, and coffee, all at incredibly affordable prices. They also have some tasty donuts available on certain days

3. The Owner is a great guy. He is exceptionally knowledgeable, incredibly friendly, and his passion for board games is infectious.

I can't wait to return and experience this gem of a place again.
reviews_data.owner_answer: We're so happy you enjoyed our spot, and appreciate the kind words about all of my rambling!

reviews_data.review_text:
Well worth your time and money. Did a great job with theming and putting high quality materials into the store. The tables are laid out very nicely and there's plenty of room for many players and groups. They have a great selection of games to play and also a nice selection of beverages and snacks. It's amazingly cheap - definitely the cheapest way to get a few hours of entertainment in the Charlotte area.

The owner is great to talk to and very passionate about the business. I will definitely be back!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for the kind words! Glad you enjoyed your time with us.

reviews_data.review_text: Great place!  Friendly owner and big tables perfect for gaming. Lots of games to choose from.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much! We're so happy you enjoyed our shop!

reviews_data.review_text: No doubt, best game store in the area.  Clean and great atmosphere. Plenty of games to buy and a great in store library to use!
reviews_data.owner_answer: We're so glad you enjoy the shop! Appreciate the kind words.

reviews_data.review_text: Super cozy shop with tons of games you can play in house. The owner was super knowledgeable and very communicative about games and rules of the games. The tables and chairs are all set up perfectly to post up and get through a lengthy game or match of whatever your heart desires!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks Dominic, appreciate the kind words and you stopping by!

reviews_data.review_text:
Fantastic Gaming Store.  I hate to say nice things about it because then I may not get a table, but it deserves every nice thing that could be said.  Great prices on MTG stuff, really awesome and put together vibe, the tables are solid and it's clear that the owner really wanted an atmosphere that is atypical of gaming stores like this, and he definitely succeeded.  Awesome selection of board games, and a super friendly owner.

Actually located behind the dentist office across the street from where the address showed in my Apple Maps app (it was showing the location over where the Walgreen's is, and that is wrong).  Maybe that will keep a few people from taking my table in the next event!

I will definitely be going back to this shop in the future.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much, we really appreciate the kinds words and are glad you enjoy the spot!

reviews_data.review_text:
Hands down the best board gaming spot in this area!

Nice game selection, cozy and well-designed space, amazing owner / host, and a convenient location - you won't be disappointed! ;)
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for the kind words Ruslan, glad you had a good time with us!

reviews_data.review_text: A friendly owner and comforting atmosphere make for a great place to relax with friends and family and unplug from the world. This is the opportunity to finally get that game you've been dying to play 'to the table.'
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you Matt for your kind words!

reviews_data.review_text: Great spot for groups and families. We went with 4 kids and everyone had a great time! Great value for an evening of fun and the owners are lovely and welcoming
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks Alex, we loved having your family in our store - hope to see you again soon!

reviews_data.review_text:
The owners are awesome
They are true gamers opening the shop to have fun and offer a chill place for like minded gamers.
See you there
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for the kind words!

reviews_data.review_text: I went in the other day to check this place out, and I was blown away. The service is extremely good, the store is very well thought out, and they have an amazing play space. Check it out if ya can.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks Theo for being an early adopter and helping get the word out! <3

reviews_data.review_text: Whether you want to play or buy games, this is the place.  One of the only shops you'll ever find that actually invested in good quality furniture and lighting so gaming there is even better than at home.  And most of their prices are lower than what you'll find on Amazon or other chain stores.  Can't recommend it enough!
Great new shop. Can quickly tell the owner is very passionate about  tabletop gaming and has built this place to be the perfect hangout spot. Will definitely be a frequent visitor!

Pros:
Owner is friendly and knowledgeable
The tables and atmosphere are warm and inviting
Has a vast amount of games

Cons:
I had to go home to my family
chill vibes and a great selection of games, hell yeah
New shop! Excited to see it grow. The Owner, "Benson", was super nice and inviting. I'll def be back! (more than my wallet or home shelf space probably would like lol)
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks Ben, we'll get everything in that wallet eventually!

reviews_data.review_text: Really cool spot. Awesome selection and a friendly, knowledgeable owner.
Cool, clean and inviting.  The owner is friendly and willing to answer questions without being too pushy.  Great selection of board games and the vibe was good.

reviews_data.review_text: Great place to play card games
They let me experience the delusion of each magic pack costing $5 in their commander sealed league (it's a blast).

This place is awesome.  I'd never have expected so much charm to fit into one little store.  I first visited for an FNM draft of Edge of Eternities with my son.  They were very accommodating of him as a new player, and we both had a great time.  The set was space themed, and my son (astute as he is) asked if some of the decor in the shop (some framed astronaut pictures and other subtle touches here and there) were set up specifically for this set.  I answered a clear and authoritative "No." I, an adult human being, seasoned in the harsh and cruel world of our time, clearly know that no one would go to such effort to do something like that, charming as it may be.

But lo!  I was quickly corrected, and, frankly, bewildered, that someone had taken the time and effort to add such a beautiful, but subtle touch for the benefit of the handful of nerds that spend their evenings turning cardboard sideways.  Since then, I've been continuously impressed with the venue, whether it be for the ambience, friendly staff, welcoming crowd, or outstanding value (a night out for two for only $30? Yes, please!)

Seriously, I can't recommend this place enough.  If you like to get your planeswalk on (they've got tons of other games to!), this is the perfect place to do it.

Chill atmosphere, chiller staff. Everyone here is extremely friendly and welcoming. They run a ton of events that are easy to join and a blast to play. I definitely recommend if you're new to board games or card games, and especially if you're looking for your local gaming store to join.
Such a great place! Steven was so helpful and the place was sooo clean and well curated!

This is such an amazing place. I came here for my first magic prerelease and it was awesome. Everyone was super friendly and the staff was so so great. Thank you guys so much!! Im already planning my trip back!

Great vibes great people the owner is super cool. Love this pace.

They have a great selection of board games, if you’re into magic the gathering they have that as well. Probably my favorite place around the area to just hang around and play board games

Went there for the first time today. Couldn’t have been a better experience. While I typically am looking for older stuff (collecting vintage RPG ephemera), a shop like this warms my heart. The shop was packed with families and friends all playing games together. A place like this just didn’t exist for me when I was a kid and if it did, it certainly wasn’t as welcoming or friendly to newcomers or non-regulars.

The two gentlemen who answered my questions were delightful and kind and even gave me a free sticker! Little things like that always make me smile. It’s clearly a hopping spot and now I have a place to go to learn one of their dozens and dozens of board games.

Also, they sell beer which, c’mon now, that’s just awesome. Great shop, great atmosphere, will be back.
Excellent cozy and comfortable space to play games and buy games!

This is business is a gem in our community.  For $5 you can get a table, borrow one of their board games (see image) and play games with your friends and family.  The staff are very welcoming and went out of their way their way to make game recommendations that were a perfect match for our group. The room with the tables was modern and very clean.  I am a middle age woman and there was no judgement, it is a space for people of all ages.  They have a private room that fits up to 10 people and you can reserve for the very reasonable price of $25.  If you like one of the games you borrow they will deduct the $5 table fee from the price of the game if you purchase.  I couldn't recommend this place more!  (Pro tip: If you want to use the tables on the weekends, plan on going after 5 pm.  They often have events during the daytime)
Thrilled to have TTT nearby - it’s a warm, welcoming space where I’ve enjoyed countless games with my kids and fellow players. No other local store creates the same sense of community.

Great shop for friends and families to enjoy board games and collectible card games like Magic and Lorcana. Employees are knowledgeable and welcoming. Great selection of drinks and snacks (craft beers and baked goods!).
I wish my town had a shop this great!
Its a great experience with a variety of both board games and trading card games.  Love coming here

I go here at least once a month with my daughter, and we ALWAYS have a great time! I always feel welcomed and I love the board game variety. I’ve learned many new games thanks to this place! It is now a tradition for me 😊

Bought cards here a few times and finally popped in - such an awesome space for games with a warm community. Folks working were super accommodating and answered any questions we had + other customers were super friendly - with those playing similar games offering a match! Family friendly, clean, air conditioned, and Star Wars fans check out the bathroom!

Absolutely love coming to To The Table! Benson and the staff are always extremely welcoming and every time I’ve come in with my now 7 month old they always ask how she’s doing and treat her like she’s one of the community since since she has been coming with me the store since she was 3 months old.

Not only are the staff and community they’ve cultivated amazing, the atmosphere in the store is also second to none. The shop is always clean, organized and stocked with so many options for Magic the Gathering.

If you’re looking for a top-tier LGS, look no further than To The Table!
The store cancelled my $1700 order because the market price went up
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hey Don - we cancelled your order immediately after you placed it, and told you why. Sorry you’re frustrated with that!

-Benson

reviews_data.review_text: Very cool place to buy board and card games. They have a good selection of games to play and games to buy. If they don’t have something in stock, the owners will order it for you. The games are reasonably priced unlike a lot of local board game stores and the owners are super cool. The store is very family friendly. The store owner tries to keep the language family friendly and my wife and I love going in there with our baby to play games. I highly recommend it.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you! Glad you enjoyed our shop ♥️

reviews_data.review_text:
Benson is the best, and TTT is my favorite game store I've ever had the pleasure of going to (and since moving to NC in 2022, I've tried every place around Charlotte).

You will always be welcomed on coming in and if you are looking for a game, they will be extremely happy (and detailed) on helping you find something to try. They have a ton of games available for you to play as part of the $5 table fee and you can play/switch games as much as you want. Seriously, if you are looking for a place to hang out with friends and play card/tabletop games, this is 100% the place to go.

Five stars for sure! My favorite place in the Charlotte area to play cards & boardgames at.

The area is clean, well-maintained, and organized. On the dozen different times I've been the staff has always been punctual & polite. Whether it's answering my questions about upcoming products, helping me to sell/trade my personal collection or even going out of their name way to custom-order things upon request it really is great experience every time.

Cannot recommend this place enough. I went here with my boyfriend for the first time, as he loves board games, and we immediately made plans to return. They have a huge selection of board games to rent at a super fair price of 5$ for a table for as long as you want, and even more games for sale at better prices than most department stores. The staff is super welcoming and friendly and checks in frequently to make sure you're enjoying your time there, even on busier days. They have lots of super cool events for all interests- my boyfriend loves strategy board games, so he attended board gaming night, and I prefer social games, so I attended Blood on the Clocktower. We've had a blast every time we go. Perfect for date nights, friend get-togethers, family outings, or even going solo and finding new friends.

Shop is a nice gem to have in the small board/card analog gaming community.

Clean, good snacks. Friendly staff. Played there a couple times with my family to add some extra players to my games.
Hands down the best game store I have ever visited. Owner and staff are all extremely friendly and accommodating. Excellent selection as well. Could not recommend highly enough

This shop is fantastic! Ive been going here for little more than a year now and partake in the weekly Friday night magic draft events and more recently blood on the clock tower. All the staff are super friendly are as dedicated to the hobby as I am. Play space is nice and spacious with an incredible selection of board games to try and buy. The private room has an incredible theme and host larger parties for their D&D or large group board games. I will be enjoying my time here for many years to come!

This place is an absolute treasure to the city. I have been to some other places but the staff and community of this store is so incredibly welcoming and a joy to be around. They have an excellent selection of games, great events occasionally, fair board game prices, etc. This place is the place to go if you are ever wanting to get into board games or are looking for others to play board games with. Thank you so much for everything yall have done.

Benson and his team are incredible. My fiancé and I have been going here since before its hard launch last year. It has been a great and consistent safe haven for all my friends and I. Super inclusive, nonjudgmental, and diverse group of fellow board game nerds 🤓
It is very apparent the owner and his staff care about the business they’re in and keeping their patrons safe. 🖤 TTT always has my business!!

Amazing place with the BEST people! If you’re looking to find a community here’s the place!

I’d also like to specifically call out my personal experience with children at the store. They host Blood on the Clocktower events on Saturdays (social deduction game) where I’ve played with a 10 year old and a 6 month old. To The Table was super inclusive and accommodating. It’s never been a problem and I’ve been going there every week since they opened.

Overall, this is a great place with great people. And delicious treats, too - Oatmeal pie is my fav!

Been there a few times.  They're setup is peak. They have a wide variety of games to purchase and play at the store, reasonably priced. Staff is always friendly. They also host occasional events welcomed to the public to play a learn/game. I've been playing a lot of the public social deduction game there, Blood on the Clock Tower.

Whether you’re a serious or casual board gamer, To The Table is a great place to have fun and meet people. The staff is so kind and welcoming and there are a lot of fun organized events to get in on. Highly recommend to anyone in the area!
Rude staff and it seems that the cafe only caters to a certain demographic. I think some players spend more time shuffling their decks than freshening up.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hey there - this appears to be related to a review we've already responded to. Sorry you feel that way!

reviews_data.review_text: I've been playing Trading Card Games for over 3 years now and have been to almost all of the Hobby shops/collectible card shops in the greater Charlotte area. I have to say that this is probably the top 2 or even 1 shop I've been to! Prices have always been fair (way better than online prices or even locally), they stock the best sleeves (Katanas) and have a great community and staff. From my experience they're primarily a Magic The Gathering store with a Star Wars Unlimited community as well. This review comes from primarily being a card game player but I know they also carry a ton of board games and have a board game player base as well!

I've never been to a game/card shop with such a good atmosphere. Employees are fair, friendly, helpful. Shop is good for kids even my smaller kids have been able to play several games from their library, and they love the bathrooms vibes :joy:
Took my two little boys Rob and Jeff to play some games and they enjoyed it. Great atmosphere and wonderful staff! Will definitely be coming back!

Best shop in town. Great selection of board games,  coffee/drinks and fresh baked goods and good vibes from owners and staff. Great Magic the Gathering scene, including sealed commander leagues, premodern , and Friday night magic always fires drafts. I go out of my way and pass other LGSs to play here.

You'll be hard pressed to find a store that is more friendly, more knowledgable, more diverse, and more stocked with any game you could want (and if they don't have it, they'll order it for you).

The staff goes above and beyond here to make sure you feel welcome every time you walk through the front door.

In an area with many great game shops, this one stands above the rest.

Discovered that their was a card/board game shop about 10 minutes from my house so I decided to check it out. I enjoy playing MTG with friends and also play yugioh and pokemon more competitively so I figured I'd check it out. As far as card games are concerned, the shop primarily focuses on MTG. Playing here has been fun and the staff is friendly and knowledgeable. A majority of the people I've played with have been kind and fun to play with as someone who doesn't typically play a ton of magic in person. The store itself is well stocked with board games/tcg products/drinks and snacks. Overall, this place is definitely a gem for board game/tcg fans in the area

Rude staff, not family friendly.

Owner and staff believe this is an adult establishment, do not bother to bring children of any ages, the ownership has made it clear they’re unwelcome.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hey there - this appears to be related to a review we've already responded to. Sorry you feel that way!

reviews_data.review_text: Fantastic store, with fantastic employees. Always welcoming super knowledgeable and very fair pricing. Highly recommend, I drive past several game stores to come here weekly. Their events and general good will towards their customers will keep me coming back

Kids not welcome. I’m very sad our visit ended horribly. The place is nicely decorated and has a great atmosphere. Prices are good and the cashier was super nice and was incredibly helpful. Unfortunately, I left crying.

Not sure if it’s the owner or manger but he seemed uncomfortable with my two small kids in the store even though they were well behaved and we kept to ourselves playing a game. After a few hours, my son needed a diaper change. There is no changing table or anyway to change a diaper in the bathroom, so I quickly and discretely, changed his diaper on the bench and threw it in the trash. We were debating which Pokémon set to get my daughter when the manager/owner came up to me and told me I can’t change a diaper on the bench and that it was completely unacceptable. I told him there was no changing table and he said they are not trying to be accommodating to people like us. He also said it was unacceptable to put “something like that” in their trash. He was so rude about it that I gathered our stuff, grabbed the diaper out of the trash and left in tears.

I’m heartbroken because I was so excited to find another game store and took my family here for Father’s Day but we will not be back. Nice store for adults but no sympathy or accommodations for children or parents. If you have little kids go to Your Local Game Store. The owner Tim has young kids, kids are welcome, and there is a changing table in the bathroom.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
I wasn't there, I was out for Father's Day with my 6 month old. We've had hundreds of families in our shop, and they are always welcome. In short, your children were disruptive, you were inappropriate, my staff told you so. You're right about one thing though - Your Local Game Store is a great establishment and I would encourage you to go there in the future.

-Benson (the owner)

reviews_data.review_text: An absolute treasure of a spot, whether you're looking to try some new board games with friends or family or looking for TCG events, owner and staff are incredible and have built a great community here
Hidden Gem

What a fantastic little spot this is locally to the wider Charlotte area. Incredibly accommodating and cozy, has a great selection of games and Magic Product and they have fostered a wonderfully supportive and welcoming community.

I went in as a first timer to commander and had a great play experience. The space is cozily lit and comfortable.

Pricing is honestly phenomenal compared to other locations within the area. I couldn’t recommend the space more to people interested in getting game time in with friends, loved ones, or even trying to meet new play groups. I will come back many many times.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you, happy to welcome you to our community!

reviews_data.review_text: This place has a great selection of games and a fun atmosphere. The owner is super friendly. The snacks are great. We love this spot for a game night.
Wonderful location to host our DnD sessions. I never thought you could win DnD until I met Mike, but if you believe in Mike, he can make anything happen ❤️!
Awesome game shop!
Friendly staff, nice selection
Dunkin was really friendly and helpful. Great games, nice atmosphere, good tables. What's not to love? My wife and I had a blast our first time here.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much! Glad you had a good time.

reviews_data.review_text:
I was in town visiting and looked up a local shop on the MTG locator in order to find a draft to play in.

I called the the store to confirm and then showed up and was amazed and how well organized and stocked the shop was.

The owner couldn't have been nicer along with the other people I met at the event. I wish I lived closer and I will be sure to go out of my way to support this shop and travel in for events when I can.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for the kind words, glad you enjoyed our shop!

reviews_data.review_text: They have a great board game and card game selection, competitive prices, and fun times to be had! This is a literal Mom and Pop store with a welcoming atmosphere and daily events, great snacks, and relaxing music to enjoy gaming to!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you Asa for the kind words!

reviews_data.review_text: This place is AMAZING! A little on the small side but great atmosphere. Mike cares about his customers and is focused on building a great gaming community. Awesome place to meet folks and play games.
Please support this business great experience!
Great place to come and try out new games
Great game store with tables to sit and play. They have some drinks and snacks to enjoy as well.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for the kind words!

reviews_data.review_text: My partner and I visited a few days ago and it felt like being in your friend's basement for game night in the best way. The owner, Mike, was welcoming to every customer, attentive with our drinks/snacks/gameplay, and knowledgable about the games. He made us feel at home and it is so so clear that a lot of love and passion went into creating To The Table. The place is BEAUTIFUL. Clean, cozy, fantasy-themed but not too over the top--there's even a special room for DND or other private events. I cannot recommend this place enough for experienced gamers and board game newbies alike. A must visit!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you, hope to see you again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: Such a chill place. Everyone there was super kind, and the board game selection was really great. It was also super clean and smelled really nice which is awesome :)
Great atmosphere, FNM draft was fun.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for stopping by, we appreciate the kind words!

reviews_data.review_text: My family went this weekend to check out this spot and I am so happy we did. The selection of games you could play and purchase were both great. Mike the owner was behind the counter and was super helpful, approachable, and genuinely kind while not being super pushy to make a purchase at all. We ended up buying a game that was new to us Agricola which Mike said a lot of "more serious" board game players have in their home collection. We did not sit down and play here yet ( we have an almost 2 year old so unsure when we will be able to do that) however there were a bunch of people playing and it looked like it was spacious, well lit, and comfortable. They have local coffee, a bunch of snacks and drinks and honestly this is just the type of spot you love to see exist in our community.
Did the bloomburrow prerelease here and it was a great experience, awesome venue
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for attending our event, we're happy you had a good time!

reviews_data.review_text: Beautiful store with great relaxing atmosphere.  Themed surprises that make you smile.  Michael Benson (the owner)  is very knowledgeable and always there to help and give advice if needed.  I would highly recommend this.  You will have a LOT of fun.
Really cool spot to meet friends and play games. Great selection of games to play along with games to buy at a great price.
reviews_data.owner_answer: We're glad you dig our place!

reviews_data.review_text: It's a fantastic place, lots of games, service is excellent, the coffee is wonderful and the price is fair and very cheap
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you! We're so glad you enjoyed your visit.

reviews_data.review_text: Absolutely wonderful and friendly place. Great place for date night!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Awesome having you with us and hope to see you again!

reviews_data.review_text:
I recently ordered some Star Wars Unlimited decks from To The Table Board Game Cafe, and I have nothing but praise for their service! Navigating their online store was a breeze, with an intuitive layout and a secure checkout process that gave me peace of mind. The range of shipping options was impressive, allowing me to choose one that perfectly suited my timeline and budget.

My cards arrived right on schedule and were carefully packed. I'm very happy with the quality of both the products and the service. This was an excellent shopping experience from start to finish, and I am definitely planning to order from them again.

Highly recommend To The Table Board Game Cafe for anyone looking for a reliable and customer-friendly game store! 5 stars all the way!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Glad you received your stuff and thank you for choosing us!

reviews_data.review_text: Omg what a great place to play games. Exciting atmosphere with an enormous volume of games to play. Mike is very knowledgeable of the entire library of games
Fantastic layout of gaming tables. Nice selection of games and cards. Friendly folks. Definitely a winner.

This is the game store I have dreamed of having in Charlotte for years now.  Owner has done everything right.  Solid wood tables, great seating, comfortable temperature even when it's 100+ degrees outside.  Great parking.  Awesome vibe - feel very comfortable being there.   Great prices on MTG.   The best MTG spot in Charlotte.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much, we're glad you love the store and so happy to have you as a new friend! 😭

reviews_data.review_text:
This place is phenomenal. It's impeccably clean, boasts a vibrant and inviting atmosphere, and offers exceptionally fair pricing. The facility is beautifully maintained, providing a quiet and cozy environment that's perfect for gaming.

Highlights:
1. Game Selection:
- The game library is extensive and meticulously curated, offering a fantastic selection of games to play.
- If you can't find what you're looking for, they have an even larger selection of games available for purchase at very competitive prices. A lot of the games here were even cheaper than what I could find online.

2. Amenities:
- They offer an array of drinks, small snacks, and coffee, all at incredibly affordable prices. They also have some tasty donuts available on certain days

3. The Owner is a great guy. He is exceptionally knowledgeable, incredibly friendly, and his passion for board games is infectious.

I can't wait to return and experience this gem of a place again.
reviews_data.owner_answer: We're so happy you enjoyed our spot, and appreciate the kind words about all of my rambling!

reviews_data.review_text:
Well worth your time and money. Did a great job with theming and putting high quality materials into the store. The tables are laid out very nicely and there's plenty of room for many players and groups. They have a great selection of games to play and also a nice selection of beverages and snacks. It's amazingly cheap - definitely the cheapest way to get a few hours of entertainment in the Charlotte area.

The owner is great to talk to and very passionate about the business. I will definitely be back!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for the kind words! Glad you enjoyed your time with us.

reviews_data.review_text: Great place!  Friendly owner and big tables perfect for gaming. Lots of games to choose from.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much! We're so happy you enjoyed our shop!

reviews_data.review_text: No doubt, best game store in the area.  Clean and great atmosphere. Plenty of games to buy and a great in store library to use!
reviews_data.owner_answer: We're so glad you enjoy the shop! Appreciate the kind words.

reviews_data.review_text: Super cozy shop with tons of games you can play in house. The owner was super knowledgeable and very communicative about games and rules of the games. The tables and chairs are all set up perfectly to post up and get through a lengthy game or match of whatever your heart desires!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks Dominic, appreciate the kind words and you stopping by!

reviews_data.review_text:
Fantastic Gaming Store.  I hate to say nice things about it because then I may not get a table, but it deserves every nice thing that could be said.  Great prices on MTG stuff, really awesome and put together vibe, the tables are solid and it's clear that the owner really wanted an atmosphere that is atypical of gaming stores like this, and he definitely succeeded.  Awesome selection of board games, and a super friendly owner.

Actually located behind the dentist office across the street from where the address showed in my Apple Maps app (it was showing the location over where the Walgreen's is, and that is wrong).  Maybe that will keep a few people from taking my table in the next event!

I will definitely be going back to this shop in the future.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much, we really appreciate the kinds words and are glad you enjoy the spot!

reviews_data.review_text:
Hands down the best board gaming spot in this area!

Nice game selection, cozy and well-designed space, amazing owner / host, and a convenient location - you won't be disappointed! ;)
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for the kind words Ruslan, glad you had a good time with us!

reviews_data.review_text: A friendly owner and comforting atmosphere make for a great place to relax with friends and family and unplug from the world. This is the opportunity to finally get that game you've been dying to play 'to the table.'
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you Matt for your kind words!

reviews_data.review_text: Great spot for groups and families. We went with 4 kids and everyone had a great time! Great value for an evening of fun and the owners are lovely and welcoming
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks Alex, we loved having your family in our store - hope to see you again soon!

reviews_data.review_text:
The owners are awesome
They are true gamers opening the shop to have fun and offer a chill place for like minded gamers.
See you there
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for the kind words!

reviews_data.review_text: I went in the other day to check this place out, and I was blown away. The service is extremely good, the store is very well thought out, and they have an amazing play space. Check it out if ya can.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks Theo for being an early adopter and helping get the word out! <3

reviews_data.review_text: Whether you want to play or buy games, this is the place.  One of the only shops you'll ever find that actually invested in good quality furniture and lighting so gaming there is even better than at home.  And most of their prices are lower than what you'll find on Amazon or other chain stores.  Can't recommend it enough!
Great new shop. Can quickly tell the owner is very passionate about  tabletop gaming and has built this place to be the perfect hangout spot. Will definitely be a frequent visitor!

The tables and atmosphere are warm and inviting
Has a vast amount of games

I had to go home to my family
chill vibes and a great selection of games, hell yeah
New shop! Excited to see it grow. The Owner, "Benson", was super nice and inviting. I'll def be back! (more than my wallet or home shelf space probably would like lol)
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks Ben, we'll get everything in that wallet eventually!

reviews_data.review_text: Really cool spot. Awesome selection and a friendly, knowledgeable owner.
Cool, clean and inviting.  The owner is friendly and willing to answer questions without being too pushy.  Great selection of board games and the vibe was good.
